  "narrative_arc": "Abused boy who fakes his own death to escape his father and rides a raft down the Mississippi with an escaped slave. Twain documents every social system they encounter — the feuding families, the con artists, the slave catchers, the \"respectable\" people who enable slavery. Huck's moral journey: deciding that saving Jim from slavery is worth going to hell.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Huck's dome maps a child navigating antebellum America with no adult protection. Layer 10 (Autonomy) is maximized — he is totally free on the raft — while Layer 1 (Legal) is hostile. His dome reveals the tension between freedom and protection for children.",
